	   <a name=10171164688003></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10171164688003><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>STOP with the PKing!!</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=153581><span id= >CrazyDruid</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 25th 11:24 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings all...<br>I have played Asheron’s Call for a long time and switched to EQ to join a friend at work that had raved about EQ – he is level 58.&nbsp;&nbsp;I joined his server (Vallon Zek) and created a druid right away. Always wanted to be a druid :-) My friend was on this same server naturally and since then I have had nothing but horrible experiences with PKing ALL DAY!!  I am not a PKer by nature.. I consistently help anyone in need, human, dwarf, gnome and of course elves (wood elf) as I am one. I started with much anticipation and total expectation for this game.  <br><br>He did not twink me as I asked not to be… I wanted to fight and build up my character as I once did on AC completely by myself.  All he did was spot me some pp to buy some spells when I made it to level 9 and then went back to his guild.<br><br>I have nothing, including money so what's the point.  I thought joining a &quot;team&quot; vs &quot;team&quot; server would include fighting in groups of different guilds or elves vs dwarves and such.  But as an elf I just keep getting attacked SOLO. I no longer worry about the mob I have to worry about the PKers.  In Gday at Kelethin they keep camping the newbie areas (orc hill) and others close by Crushbone.  I went to Quynos and got PKed 13 times in a row in front of the bank even though I told all 10 of the humans that I was leaving their fair city.  They took the only 3 pp i had and just kept waiting for me to respawn right in front of the bank since i was bound there (bad idea).<br><br>I am not complaining by this -- I know this is a PvP server but what is the difference between team and pvp at this rate????? none!! I even helped out a Necro by healing him only as he was getting mashed by 3 grizzlies in WK and then he rested, and proceeded to attack me cause I was an elf.  What type of playing is this??  I grouped with an elf and a human and a gnome at the beginning and while we were playing the gnome attacked me.. so not only did I have to fight the mob but also him.  This is ludicrous!!<br><br>I joined a guild right away when I started and have received little help if any.  What are some strategies for a druid to fight melee class opponents.  I can’t get my spells off quick enough before getting stunned or interrupted… I can’t fight 3 of them as it’s always more than one against me.  I don’t mind fighting in an arena but NOT when I am on a monster fighting and some dwarf starts attacking me from the rear.  I guess I should have just gone on a non PvP server but now I am a 12th level Druid and become rather close to him.  Arghh.. sigh..  any ideas or recommendations or strategies for a druid would be great.  I guess at lower levels we don’t stand a chance…. Or I need more practice.  I just find that I need to mem one set of spells for Pvp and different ones for mobs.. this makes it rather hard.<br><br>Sorry about the length of this post.. <br><br>CrazyDruid (12th season)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>A lone Druid of the 12th season</td></tr>
