	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well I have some tidbits of advice but cannot help you with your druid problem, because I have never played one. <br><br>I also play on a pvp server, and I LOVE IT.. Wouldn't play another server.&nbsp;&nbsp;Tallon Zek btw.  I had the same problem with my SK, got pk'd alot, but when your druid lvl's higher, you will be a pk king.  So stick with him.  Now with your decision to be on a pvp server, You will want to be twinked... Sorry buddy, but it that or die alot.  I started out the same way, &quot;I'll do it on my own&quot;  That crap got old really quick.  Noone messes with me now unless they out lvl the hell out of me..  I say, take some help from your friend.  Let him give you some good resist gear at least, and some mana items.  <br><br>You say you like to help people, but be careful who your helping, think about it.  They are enemies, they are adversaries to you none the less, make sure they ask for help.  You may run into less problems about being stabbed in the back.  It sux, I've seen it happen alot.  BTW, it's called X teaming when you help races your not alligned with, and some players look down on it. Like myself.  <br><br>Problem with your guild not helping.  Leave them.  Don't just join the first guild you see.  Search for one, make sure they take care of their peoples, make a guild choose you through your playing skill.  Keep doing good jobs in your groups and have fun with people and you'll see that a better guild will find you...  Being in a guild isn't about having a tag over your head, it's about being there for eachother.  IMHO.<br><br>I hope some of this helps, I know I tend to ramble.  Good Luck..  <br><br>Scyinide<br>Shadow Knight<br>41st Season<br>Tallon Zek<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
